article.headline: Duquesne 111, La Salle 105
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Reggie Jackson scored a career-best 23 points and made all seven of his free throw attempts to lead Duquesne to a 111-105 victory over La Salle on Wednesday night. Aaron Jackson scored 22 and Kieron Achara 17 for Duquesne (10-11,6-4 Atlantic 10), which had six players score in double figures on the way to its fifth straight victory. Darnell Harris scored 20 points, and Rodney Green and Kimmani Barrett added 18 each for the Explorers (9-15,2-8 Atlantic 10), who lost their fourth straight despite a season-high point total. The Dukes faced a 10-point deficit at the break and opened the second half with a 10-3 run, closing within 60-59 with 17:45 remaining. Duquesne took its first lead at 73-72 with 12:50 left. La Salle rallied and regained the lead at 80-79 with 10:01 remaining. A dunk by Aaron Jackson with 1:07 left gave Duquesne a 104-103 lead with 1:07 remaining. Harris hit a runner that put La Salle on top 105-104 with 46 seconds remaining before Reggie and Aaron Jackson combined to score the Dukes' final 19 points, including the last seven from the free throw line. The Explorers jumped out to a 10-0 lead at the start of the game and shot 20-for-32 in the first half, including 7-for-8 from 3-point range. Duquesne's leading scorer, Robert Mitchell, was limited to three points on 1-for-8 shooting.
